{
    "publish_date": "2012-10-15T15:39:28.000Z", 
    "video_length": "PT4M9S", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "Hexaflexagons-- they&#39;re\ncool, hip, and hexa-fun", 
            "dur": "2.41", 
            "start": "0.5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to play with, right?", 
            "dur": "1.39", 
            "start": "2.91"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Wrong.", 
            "dur": "0.84", 
            "start": "4.3"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Hexaflexagons are not toys.", 
            "dur": "1.37", 
            "start": "5.14"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "With the increasing number of\nhexaflexagons finding their way", 
            "dur": "2.12", 
            "start": "6.51"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "into homes and schools,\nit&#39;s important to be aware", 
            "dur": "2.083", 
            "start": "8.63"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of proper flexagation\nregulations", 
            "dur": "1.457", 
            "start": "10.713"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "when engaging in flexagon\nconstruction and use.", 
            "dur": "2.31", 
            "start": "12.17"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Taking proper precautions can\nhelp avoid a flexa-catastrophe.", 
            "dur": "3.42", 
            "start": "14.48"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Do not wear loose clothing\nwhen engaging in flexagation.", 
            "dur": "2.76", 
            "start": "17.9"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If you have long\nhair, tie it back,", 
            "dur": "1.5", 
            "start": "20.66"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "so it doesn&#39;t get caught\nin a flexagation device.", 
            "dur": "2.041", 
            "start": "22.16"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Ties are also a common\nsource of incidents.", 
            "dur": "2.249", 
            "start": "24.201"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Stay alert.", 
            "dur": "0.91", 
            "start": "26.45"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Never flexagate while\nunder the influence.", 
            "dur": "1.98", 
            "start": "27.36"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "When using a hexaflexagon,\nsudden unexpected sides", 
            "dur": "2.5", 
            "start": "29.34"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "may appear, and drugs like\nalcohol can slow reaction time.", 
            "dur": "2.849", 
            "start": "31.84"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If you aren&#39;t sure what kind of\nflexagon you&#39;re dealing with,", 
            "dur": "2.541", 
            "start": "34.689"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it&#39;s safer to temporarily\ndisable the flexagon.", 
            "dur": "2.69", 
            "start": "37.23"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Flexagons can be disarmed\nby using scissors", 
            "dur": "1.8", 
            "start": "39.92"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to cut them apart.", 
            "dur": "0.83", 
            "start": "41.72"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You can cut across\nthe original seam", 
            "dur": "1.5", 
            "start": "42.55"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "where the paper strip\nwas taped together,", 
            "dur": "1.48", 
            "start": "44.05"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which may appear on the\nedge or through the face", 
            "dur": "1.999", 
            "start": "45.53"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of the flexagon.", 
            "dur": "0.891", 
            "start": "47.529"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In an emergency,\nhowever, flexagons", 
            "dur": "1.51", 
            "start": "48.42"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "can be cut apart right through\na triangle, or on three edges", 
            "dur": "3.09", 
            "start": "49.93"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "if you want to retain symmetry,\nor into nine separate triangles", 
            "dur": "2.71", 
            "start": "53.02"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "if you really want to be safe.", 
            "dur": "1.56", 
            "start": "55.73"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You can even cut them in half\ndown the length of the paper", 
            "dur": "2.416", 
            "start": "57.29"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "strip like this,\ninto two separate--", 
            "dur": "2.694", 
            "start": "59.706"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Once you cut your\nflexagon apart,", 
            "dur": "1.411", 
            "start": "62.4"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "you can figure out\nwhat kind it is.", 
            "dur": "1.458", 
            "start": "63.811"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If it has nine triangles,\nthat&#39;s 18 triangle sides.", 
            "dur": "2.31", 
            "start": "65.269"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So at six triangles\nper hexagon side,", 
            "dur": "1.541", 
            "start": "67.579"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that&#39;s three sides\nof trihexaflexagon.", 
            "dur": "2.38", 
            "start": "69.12"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Note that some\nflexagons might be", 
            "dur": "1.492", 
            "start": "71.5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "made from a double strip of\ntriangles that have been folded", 
            "dur": "2.458", 
            "start": "72.992"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in half, so that marker\ndoesn&#39;t bleed through.", 
            "dur": "2.28", 
            "start": "75.45"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Don&#39;t let yourself be fooled\nby the extra triangles.", 
            "dur": "3.16", 
            "start": "77.73"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Avoid danger during\nhexaflexagon construction.", 
            "dur": "2.475", 
            "start": "80.89"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If you&#39;re not working\nfrom a printed pattern,", 
            "dur": "1.875", 
            "start": "83.365"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "you might start your\nflexagon by picking a point", 
            "dur": "1.84", 
            "start": "85.24"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "on the edge of a strip of\npaper, folding that 180 degree", 
            "dur": "2.49", 
            "start": "87.08"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "angle into thirds to\ncreate 360 degree angles,", 
            "dur": "3.054", 
            "start": "89.57"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and then using the equilateral\ntriangle that results", 
            "dur": "2.166", 
            "start": "92.624"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "as a guide to fold the\nrest of the strip of paper,", 
            "dur": "2.53", 
            "start": "94.79"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "zigzagging back and forth.", 
            "dur": "1.54", 
            "start": "97.32"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Without proper\nattention and focus,", 
            "dur": "1.95", 
            "start": "98.86"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "this could easily lead to\nbecoming unreasonably amused", 
            "dur": "2.92", 
            "start": "100.81"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "with the springy spring of\nhappy triangles that results.", 
            "dur": "2.94", 
            "start": "103.73"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Always keep your hexaflexagon\nin good working order.", 
            "dur": "2.9", 
            "start": "106.67"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Pre-creasing all the\ntriangles both ways", 
            "dur": "1.7", 
            "start": "109.57"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "before configuring them into\nhexaflexagonal formation", 
            "dur": "2.5", 
            "start": "111.27"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "will help your flexagon operate\nproperly and avoid accidents.", 
            "dur": "3.18", 
            "start": "113.77"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Keep a close watch on the\nchirality of your hexaflexagon.", 
            "dur": "3", 
            "start": "116.95"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That is, whether it is\nright or left handed.", 
            "dur": "2.47", 
            "start": "119.95"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Notice how in this\nhexaflexagon, water flows", 
            "dur": "2.4", 
            "start": "122.42"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "clockwise down under\nthe flaps, even", 
            "dur": "1.85", 
            "start": "124.82"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "if you flip it over or flex it.", 
            "dur": "1.54", 
            "start": "126.67"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well, in this hexaflexagon,\nit flows counter-clockwise.", 
            "dur": "2.89", 
            "start": "128.21"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "They&#39;re mirror images.", 
            "dur": "1.46", 
            "start": "131.1"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The chirality is decided\nwhen you fold and tape", 
            "dur": "2.41", 
            "start": "132.56"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "your triangles into a\ntwisty loop, and once taped,", 
            "dur": "2.11", 
            "start": "134.97"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it is impossible\nto change from one", 
            "dur": "1.76", 
            "start": "137.08"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to the other without\ncutting it apart,", 
            "dur": "1.73", 
            "start": "138.84"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "at least in three-dimensional\neuclidean space.", 
            "dur": "2.58", 
            "start": "140.57"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "A change in chirality\ncould be a sign", 
            "dur": "1.812", 
            "start": "143.15"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that your flexagon\nhas been flipped", 
            "dur": "1.458", 
            "start": "144.962"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "through four-dimensional\nspace and is possibly a highly", 
            "dur": "2.291", 
            "start": "146.42"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "dangerous\nmulti-dimensional portal.", 
            "dur": "1.969", 
            "start": "148.711"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "With experience, a\nhexaflexagon master", 
            "dur": "2.27", 
            "start": "150.68"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "can construct a hexaflexagon\nin mere seconds.", 
            "dur": "2.55", 
            "start": "152.95"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Some forgo tape and\nscissors entirely", 
            "dur": "1.88", 
            "start": "155.5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "by folding a double\nstrip that&#39;s too long", 
            "dur": "1.82", 
            "start": "157.38"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and tucking the extra in.", 
            "dur": "1.55", 
            "start": "159.2"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This is an advanced\ntechnique that should not", 
            "dur": "2.34", 
            "start": "160.75"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "be attempted without\nprior training.", 
            "dur": "2.27", 
            "start": "163.09"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Beware topological changes.", 
            "dur": "1.99", 
            "start": "165.36"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This family seems safe\nfrom this philosoraptor,", 
            "dur": "2.319", 
            "start": "167.35"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "because they live\non separate planets", 
            "dur": "1.541", 
            "start": "169.669"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "with a cold, empty vacuum\nof space between them.", 
            "dur": "2.34", 
            "start": "171.21"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But after a single flex,\nthe unfortunate victims", 
            "dur": "2.18", 
            "start": "173.55"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "are now doomed, protected only\nby the inconsequential barrier", 
            "dur": "3.27", 
            "start": "175.73"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of their domicile.", 
            "dur": "1.4", 
            "start": "179"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Your stars might explode,\nyour frowns may become smiles,", 
            "dur": "2.372", 
            "start": "180.4"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "your most pointy\nof triangles might", 
            "dur": "1.458", 
            "start": "182.772"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "become the roundest of circles.", 
            "dur": "1.6", 
            "start": "184.23"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Perfectly healthy snakes\nmay turn into snake loops,", 
            "dur": "2.28", 
            "start": "185.83"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "or worse, become decapitated.", 
            "dur": "2.13", 
            "start": "188.11"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Either state is\nfatal for the snake,", 
            "dur": "1.97", 
            "start": "190.24"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "as having no head can\nlead to starvation.", 
            "dur": "2.45", 
            "start": "192.21"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This can be avoided by simply\nmarking where connections will", 
            "dur": "2.52", 
            "start": "194.66"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "be across neighboring\ntriangles first.", 
            "dur": "2.31", 
            "start": "197.18"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Afterwards, the lines can be\nfilled in however you like.", 
            "dur": "2.98", 
            "start": "199.49"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Be aware that with\nthe trihexaflexagon,", 
            "dur": "1.89", 
            "start": "202.47"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "there are two\nvariations to each face.", 
            "dur": "2.057", 
            "start": "204.36"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So you can simply draw one\nside where triangles connect,", 
            "dur": "2.333", 
            "start": "206.417"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and flip and draw the other.", 
            "dur": "1.166", 
            "start": "208.75"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But in the hexa-hexaflexagon,\nthe main three", 
            "dur": "1.874", 
            "start": "209.916"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "faces each appear\nfour different ways.", 
            "dur": "2.43", 
            "start": "211.79"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If you use hexaflexagons,\nkeep an eye", 
            "dur": "1.8", 
            "start": "214.22"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "out for signs of dependency.", 
            "dur": "1.59", 
            "start": "216.02"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Overuse can lead to addiction\nand possibly an overdose.", 
            "dur": "3.12", 
            "start": "217.61"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Some users of hexaflexagons\nreport confusion,", 
            "dur": "2.54", 
            "start": "220.73"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "mind-blown syndrome,\nhexaflexaperplexia,", 
            "dur": "2.48", 
            "start": "223.27"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "hexaflexadyslexia,\nhexaflexaperfectionism,", 
            "dur": "2.8", 
            "start": "225.75"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and\nhexaflexa-Mexican-food-cravings.", 
            "dur": "2.05", 
            "start": "228.55"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If you find yourself\nexperiencing", 
            "dur": "1.52", 
            "start": "230.6"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "any of these symptoms, stop\nflexagon use immediately,", 
            "dur": "2.71", 
            "start": "232.12"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and see the head of\nyour math department.", 
            "dur": "1.98", 
            "start": "234.83"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "With proper\nprecautions, flexagating", 
            "dur": "1.8", 
            "start": "236.81"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "can be a great\npart of your life.", 
            "dur": "1.667", 
            "start": "238.61"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Follow these simple\nsafety guidelines,", 
            "dur": "1.583", 
            "start": "240.277"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and you should be ready for\na fun and safe hexaflexagon", 
            "dur": "2.55", 
            "start": "241.86"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "experience.", 
            "dur": "1.55", 
            "start": "244.41"
        }
    ], 
